    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"告别 carries deeper emotional weight than casual goodbyes. In Chinese culture, formal farewells are\nimportant rituals, especially for significant life transitions. The concept often implies a\nmeaningful or potentially permanent parting, making it more solemn than everyday \"see you later\"\nexpressions."}],"type":"paragraph"}
